An enchanted lyre(i) is an enchanted lyre that contains infinite teleport charges to Rellekka. When the hard Fremennik Diary is completed, the lyre can also teleport to Waterbirth Island, and gains the ability to teleport to Jatizso and Neitiznot after completion of the elite Fremennik Diary. After upgrading with hard and elite diaries you will lose the ability to left-click teleport, thus making it not ideal for emergency situations.

Players can imbue their un-enchanted lyre after completion of The Fremennik Trials by offering Fossegrimen a one-off offering of 1,000 raw sharks, raw bass, raw manta rays and raw sea turtles, costing 3,236,000. Fossegrimen will accept both noted and un-noted offerings, and they can be given in increments; she will inform players of the remaining amount required to imbue the lyre.

The offering cost will drop by 200 raw fish (647,200) for each tier of the Fremennik Diary completed. However, she will not return any fish once a higher tier of the diary has been completed.

Should players lose the imbued lyre, they can obtain another un-enchanted lyre and summon Fossegrimen, where she will imbue the lyre free of charge.

While equipped, the colour of the lyre's middle section is the same as the player's shoe colour.

A player plays the lyre to teleport to the Fremennik Province.

[[File:Enchanted lyre(i) detail.png|left|150x150px]]
An '''enchanted lyre(i)''' is an [[enchanted lyre]] that contains infinite [[teleport]] charges to [[Rellekka]]. When the [[hard Fremennik Diary]] is completed, the lyre can also teleport to [[Waterbirth Island]], and gains the ability to teleport to [[Jatizso]] and [[Neitiznot]] after completion of the [[elite Fremennik Diary]]. After upgrading with hard and elite diaries you will lose the ability to left-click teleport, thus making it not ideal for emergency situations.

Players can imbue their un-enchanted [[lyre]] after completion of [[The Fremennik Trials]] by offering [[Fossegrimen]] a one-off offering of 1,000 [[raw shark]]s, [[raw bass]], [[raw manta ray]]s and [[raw sea turtle]]s, costing {{Coins|{{GEP|Raw shark|1000}}+{{GEP|Raw bass|1000}}+{{GEP|Raw manta ray|1000}}+{{GEP|Raw sea turtle|1000}}}}. Fossegrimen will accept both noted and un-noted offerings, and they can be given in increments; she will inform players of the remaining amount required to imbue the lyre.

The offering cost will drop by 200 raw fish ({{Coins|{{GEP|Raw shark|200}}+{{GEP|Raw bass|200}}+{{GEP|Raw manta ray|200}}+{{GEP|Raw sea turtle|200}}}}) for each tier of the [[Fremennik Diary]] completed. However, she will not return any fish once a higher tier of the diary has been completed.

Should players lose the imbued lyre, they can obtain another un-enchanted lyre and summon [[Fossegrimen]], where she will imbue the lyre free of charge.

While equipped, the colour of the lyre's middle section is the same as the player's shoe colour.

[[File:Lyre teleport.gif|thumb|200px|A player plays the lyre to teleport to the [[Fremennik Province]].]]
